title: What happens between now and Inauguration Day
description: Americans who went to the polls on Election Day don't actually select the President directly.

title: John King on the Election Week wait, math and his Magic Wall
description: Election Week in America might have taken nearly 100 hours to produce a new President but one winner was clear for days: CNN's indefatigable Chief National Correspondent John King, who explained America's complex electoral math and the political idiosyncrasies of obscure counties to the world at his Magic Wall.

title: World leaders congratulate Joe Biden
description: World leaders have congratulated President-elect Joe Biden and Vice President-elect Kamala Harris Saturday after Biden declared victory in the 2020 election, with many striking a jubilant tone on social media.

title: Biden wins election he made about the character of Trump and the nation
description: America has chosen Democrat Joe Biden as its 46th president, CNN projects, turning to a veteran voice who has projected calm and compassion, promised a more empathetic and scientific approach to the pandemic, and pledged to stabilize American politics after four years of Donald Trump's White House chaos.

title: Vice President-elect Kamala Harris represents a new face of political power
description: Kamala Harris, who on Saturday became America's first female, first Black and first South Asian vice president-elect, represents a new face of political power after an election all about who wields power and how they use it.

title: This Muslim basketball player refused to take off her hijab, opening new doors for athletes of other faiths
